items.label: I know when I need help with my health.
I am comfortable talking to a health care professional about any issue, including sensitive ones.
I must solve other problems first before I can focus on my own health.
I believe I will be healthier if I follow the advice I am given.
I believe I will be healthier if I follow the advice I am given.
I try new approaches to find the best way to manage my health.
I know what I need to measure regularly in order to be healthy.
I can maintain all the lifestyle changes needed to improve my health, even under stress.
I have someone close to me to help me manage my health.
I know when something gets in the way of improving my health.
I believe family and friends will adapt their lifestyles to support changes I make.
I am able to maintain my actions to improve my health over the long term.
I always understand the reason(s) why I'm prescribed a medication.
I believe I can find the best solutions for my health condition(s).
I come prepared to my medical appointments with questions to ask.
I understand the cause(s) of my health condition(s).
I feel certain of how I can improve my health.
I use a tracker to record and measure my progress.
I see how I should adjust my lifestyle to improve my health.
I am most responsible for managing my health.
I take medication exactly as directed, whenever it is prescribed for me.
